dict.infinite.steno defines a programmatic steno corpus for javelin that is never flattened into a simple stroke→text map. Instead, it describes unbounded generic types and parametric functions via @type families, @count banks, and @fuse directives that are compiled by `build-javelin` into two small lookup tables (types and constructs), then replayed per stroke by StenoGeneratedDictionary's append walk.

The append set lives in the `## types` section: each @type record (stroke, arity, text with %t argument markers) can nest arbitrarily deep — unlike dict.steno's Pass B, which restricts arity-0 generics. `````STKWR-T```` is a standalone type emitter that forms the differential test pin between expand_dict (its shallow pool-depth subset is enumerable) and the runtime walker. The function family uses @count AOEU (0..15 parameters) and @fuse to merge a return type %T into the shape stroke, avoiding T^n explosion: the fuse fills the return slot first (stroking it immediately after the base), then each parameter in template order. Vocabulary is docs/steno-format.md plus %T (D11), the fuse-target type slot; docs/pipeline.md "The reference walker" documents the fill order and lookup replay.